<h2>Default list styles</h2>

<p>
  If you need an unordered, ordered, or definition list for inclusion in your site's regular body copy,
  then use the <%= highlight_html_example("<ul>") %>, <%= highlight_html_example("<ol>") %>,
  or <%= highlight_html_example("<dl>") %> elements <strong>without any extra HTML classes</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  The following list implementations are only to be used in cases where your lists require a little more presentational flair.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Plain Lists</h2>

<p>One use for plain lists is to create a series of text links in your page footers.</p>

<%= render_example do %>
<ul class="c-list c-list--plain">
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--plain"><a href="#">Red</a></li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--plain"><a href="#">Blue</a></li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--plain"><a href="#">Turquoise</a></li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--plain"><a href="#">Teal</a></li>
</ul>
<% end %>

<hr>

<h2>Green Bullet Lists</h2>

<%= render_example do %>
<ul class="c-list c-list--bulleted">
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">Red</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">Blue</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">Turquoise</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted">Teal</li>
</ul>
<% end %>

<p>There is also a larger variant of this bulleted list:</p>

<%= render_example do %>
<ul class="c-list c-list--bulleted c-list--large">
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted c-list__item--large">Red</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted c-list__item--large">Blue</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted c-list__item--large">Turquoise</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--bulleted c-list__item--large">Teal</li>
</ul>
<% end %>

<hr>

<h2>Horizontal List</h2>

<%= render_example do %>
<ul class="c-list c-list--horiz">
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--horiz">Red</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--horiz">Blue</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--horiz">Turquoise</li>
  <li class="c-list__item c-list__item--horiz">Teal</li>
</ul>
<% end %>

<hr>

<h2>Horizontal Definition List</h2>

<%= render_example do %>
<dl class="c-def-list">
  <dt class="c-def-list__term">Red</dt>
  <dd class="c-def-list__definition">Lorem Ipsum Dolor Sit Amet</dd>
  <dt class="c-def-list__term">Blue</dt>
  <dd class="c-def-list__definition">Lorem Ipsum Dolor Sit Amet</dd>
  <dt class="c-def-list__term">Turquoise</dt>
  <dd class="c-def-list__definition">Lorem Ipsum Dolor Sit Amet</dd>
  <dt class="c-def-list__term">Teal</dt>
  <dd class="c-def-list__definition">Lorem Ipsum Dolor Sit Amet</dd>
</dl>
<% end %>

<h2>Icon List</h2>

<p>
  Each bullet has an accompanying icon, which is specified from <%= link_to "the range included
  in these assets", page_path('styles', 'icons') %>. Name it in your HTML class like this:
  <%= highlight_sass_example('c-list__item--icon-twitter') %>, where "twitter" is the name of the icon.
  Change that word to any one of the available icons to customise your list items.
</p>

<% for icon in icons %>

<p><%= highlight_sass_example(".c-icon--#{icon}") %></p>

<%= render_example do %>
<ul class="c-icon-list">
  <li class="c-icon-list__item">
    <span class="c-icon c-icon--large c-icon--<%= icon %>"></span>
    <span class="c-icon-list__text">List Item Text Goes Here List Item Text Goes Here List Item Text Goes Here List Item Text Goes Here List Item Text Goes Here List Item Text Goes Here</span>
  </li>
</ul>
<% end %>

<% end %>
